\sqrt{x+\sqrt{2x-1}}+\sqrt{x-\sqrt{2x-1}}=\sqrt{2}
\sqrt{2}
2x-1=u^2
u \ge 0
x=(u^2+1)/2
x+\sqrt{2x-1}=\frac{u^2+2u+1}{2}.
x-\sqrt{2x-1}=\frac{u^2-2u+1}{2}.
\sqrt{x+\sqrt{2x-1}} +\sqrt{x-\sqrt{2x-1}}=\frac{|u+1|}{\sqrt{2}}+\frac{|u-1|}{\sqrt{2}}.
|u+1|+|u-1|=2.
|u+1|=u+1
u \ge 1
|u-1|=u-1
u=1
x=1
0 \le u <1
|u-1|=1-u
2=2
u
1/2\le x<1
x
1/2\le x\le 1
